  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b2da2dd5269cbbc49898722278a6311c, type: 3}
  m_Name: Storage Tank
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  componentName: Storage Tank
  specifications: (Source Tank)
  description: "Stores the working fluid and supplies it to the flow rig system during
    operation.\n\nWater Return Direction\n\na. Water will flow from the second tank
    to the first tank through Valve 11, passing through the E+H Liquiphant FTL31
    Pressure Transmitter. This transmitter measures the water\npressure in the pipeline.\nb.
    The water then passes through a strainer filter before being pumped back via
    the Grundfos UP20-45 N 150 in-line pump. The flow rate can be adjusted using
    the Arita 1\u201D Gate Valve located downstream of the pump.\nc. Subsequently,
    the water flows through the Arita-107 SE Pressure Relief Valve. Should the pipeline
    pressure exceed 150 psi, the valve diverts water to the balancing pipe to safely
    reduce the pressure.\nd. Finally, the water passes through a check valve before
    re-entering the first tank via Valve 3. This check valve ensures unidirectional
    flow, preventing backflow within the system."
